    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-06-23T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-06-23T17:00:00-05:00" n="374"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5531/773c: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davies</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-23T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 23, 1939—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>40. The Department wishes to know whether the Belgian Government is interested,
                    in principle, in negotiating a revised trade agreement <pb facs="0433" n="425"
                        xml:id="pg_425"/> as proposed in the memorandum handed to the Belgian
                    Ambassador here on May 19, 1939. While we realize, of course, that further time
                    for study may be required before the Belgians can give us a definitive reply, we
                    would be glad to know if the Belgian Government is sufficiently interested in
                    our proposal to justify our continuing the statistical studies on which the two
                    preliminary lists attached to our memorandum of May 19 are based. Please reply
                    by cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
